THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DELEGATED CONTROL OF MANAGEMENT DUTIES TO WESTMINSTER SERVICES, INC. AN AFFILIATED NOT-FOR-PROFIT. WESTMINSTER SERVICES, INC. HAS EXTENSIVE EXPERIENCE WITH THE MANAGEMENT OF NOT-FOR-PROFIT HOMES FOR THE AGED.
THE SOLE MEMBER OF THE ORGANIZATION IS WESTMINSTER RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES, INC.
WESTMINSTER RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES, INC. MAY ELECT ONE OR MORE MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
WESTMINSTER RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES, INC. MUST APPROVE DISSOLUTION OF THE ORGANIZATION, SALE OF SUBSTANTIAL ASSETS, NEW BOARD MEMBERS OR REPLACEMENT OF THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY.
THE AUDIT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS THE 990 BEFORE IT IS FILED.

THE WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS REVIEWED AND SIGNED ANNUALLY BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES. WITH A CENTRALIZED ACCOUNTS PAYABLE AND PAYROLL SYSTEM, THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY MONITORS ALL PAYMENTS AND TRANSACTIONS WITH VENDORS. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION HAS A TOLL-FREE COMPLIANCE HOTLINE THAT CAN BE USED BY BOARD MEMBERS OR STAFF TO REPORT ANY ISSUES.
THE ORGANIZATION UTILIZES NUMEROUS SALARY SURVEYS WITH LIKE-KIND ORGANIZATIONS TO DETERMINE THE PROPER SALARY/WAGE AMOUNT FOR EACH EMPLOYEE.
THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
AVERAGE HOURS PER WEEK ARE SHARED BETWEEN THE RELATED ORGANIZATIONS OF WESTMINSTER RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES, INC. AND PRESBYTERIAN RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES, INC.
